            "answer_text": "Yes, I\u2019d think that one could read Introduction to Algorithms in a day. You wouldn\u2019t understand much of it, however. If you want to read and understand the book, then I recommend that you read it on Venus. On Venus, one day takes 5832 hours, or 243 Earth days. That should be doable. If you really apply yourself, you might be able to read the book in one day on Mercury: 1408 hours, or 58 2/3 Earth days. The only other planet in our solar system whose day takes longer than an Earth day is Mars, where a day takes 25 hours. That won\u2019t be enough to read and understand Introduction to Algorithms. ",
